	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay bro, bear with me as I try to lead you there from point A (dock) to B (fort). I have only run this course once so if you find a quicker way, then there ya go =). <br><br>(edited) I was so in a hurry to help I just realized that you know how to get to the town already so...Just skip to the part where you get in the fort. They WILL drop the flicker of lava and sea but it MAY take 1-2 hours. And if you get lucky, you will get a very nice shm/rog/brd/sk/dru/monk/clr back item with stats(hope I got it all right. I not just keep checking the beastiary page as I will post the exact stats there as soon as I get home.) item to sell off of a named luggald by the name of Rite Master Rinsomethingorother.<br><br>*for all others read on*<br><br>First jump into the water heading south by southeast (when you get in you will need to adjust). Once on the beach go around the left side of that cracked ship as you are facing it. I want to say go to where the first big rock is and head to up hill. as you go up hill you should see some emancipated trolls of the undead kind. They agro, kill them and be done with it. Ahead of you should be a corral (sp?) looking thing, kinda like the thing you see horses in on t.v. shows all gathered up for taming. <br><br>There will be some skellies inhabiting this area just cut a hard right from here. On the right side of you there is some sort of formation, be it boat or otherwise and in front of you should be the mountain that you need to get to. Look up and if you see what look like large stepping stones jutting out from the rock, you are in the right spot...just go about half right from here, continuously heading for the wall. Upon hitting the wall you need to find the tunnel that will take ya to the little town thingy. In the tunnel are a few lb mobs easy kills. Keep an eye out for your left side and when you see a large opening (floor to ceiling), make that left. You are now in the town.<br><br>Once in the town, you will see the fort in front of you in the distance. Just make your way right and kill as you go. Adds will not harm you if you have at least 2 others with you. When you get to the big cluster of huts, you will see the entrance to the fort guarded by either the troll mystics or warriors. Kill them and enter the fort. In the center of the fort is the room where the luggalds pop. You HAVE to go through at least an hour to 2 hours of spawns to kill them enough times for your drops.<br><br>You know the spawn is started again when the 2 out front pop (warrior trolls and mystics. usually one or the other, only 2 mobs) They have laughable hp at lvl 55 with Char cast and hit decently. However I am a battle mage and will go toe to toe ;). (I also have regen 3, run 3 and use phantom armor too, LOL.) If they beat on you, kite in small circles till your pet gets agro.<br><br>I hope this helps you as I am going based on pure memory of having only been there once. Post me back and tell me how it goes for you.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb 26 13:38:53 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Baron Sirulus, Mage of the 58th Chapter<br>~Tunare Server~ <br>a.k.a <br>Sir De <br>Anon`erdin</td></tr>
